tourBios.carHigh:
2015: Joined PGA TOUR Latinoamérica with a T21 finish at Q-School in Lima, Peru in January… Made the cut in 11 of 14 starts, collecting four top-10s to finish the PGA TOUR Latinoamérica season ranked 24th on the Order of Merit… His best finish was T2 at the All You Need is Ecuador Open, where he trailed tournament winner Ricardo Celia by three strokes in September… His other top-5 was a T4 at the Lexus Panama Classic in May… Carded a season low 64 (-8) in round 2 of the Honduras Open, where he finished T7 in May… Also finished T7 at the season opening Avianca Colombia Open in March… A T2 finish at Web.com Tour Q-School final in December secured him strong status for 2016.

2014: Turned pro in June, making his debut with a missed cut at the Web.com Tour's Cleveland Open.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Played college golf at the University of Oklahoma (2010-14)… Named All-American in 2014… Had one college win by finishing T1 at the Royal Oaks Intercollegiate in October, 2012… Won the 2013 Cotton States Invitational... In 2010, while at Deer Creek High School, he was named an All-State pick by the Oklahoma Coaches Association… Posted a 5-under 67 that include a hole-in-one to win the Oklahoma All-State Tournament by five shots... Won the 2010 Oklahoma Junior Amateur title.
tourBios.personal: Enjoys hunting and fishing in his free time…Favorite memory in golf is making a hole-in-one with his dad when he was age 8..Has two brothers, Cameron and Braden… His father, Randy, who is a Christian minister, introduced him to the game when he was a toddler… Jim Woodward is his golf instructor… Carries a OSU headcover… Favorite course he has played is Muirfield Village… His favorite teams are Oklahoma State and the Oklahoma City Thunder… “The Big Bang Theory” and “Arrow” are his favorite TV shows… “American Sniper” and “Gladiator” are his favorite movies… Country music signer Jason Aldean is his top entertainer… Enjoys Mexican food… Roger Federer and Tiger Woods are his favorite athletes to watch… The beach is his top vacation spot… The Bible is his favorite book… Personal motto is a verse from The Bible, John 3:30: “He must become greater; I must become less.”… Twitter: @IanDavisOSU… Instagram: @iandavis1010

tourBios.exmtStatus: Finished T2 at 2015 Web.com Tour Qualifying Tournament
